asing emphasis on ethics the culmination of ideas in her earlier work? How do ethics relate to politics in her work, and how do they connect to her increasing concern with violence, war and conflict?Butler and Ethics breaks new ground in scholarship on Butler and will also advance on-going debates about materiality and the body, biopolitics, affect theory, precariousness and subjectification.Contributors Birgit Schippers • Catherine Mills • Drew Walker • Fiona Jenkins • Moya Lloyd • Nathan Gies • Samuel A. Chambers • Sara RushingKey FeaturesExplores the relation between politics and ethics in Butler’s writingsExplores Butler’s understanding of the body in relation to both politics and ethics, feminist and non-feministLooks at work from the full span of Butler’s career up to Frames of War  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aEthics. 0aSocial ethics. 4aPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aChambers, Samuel A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGies, Nathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJenkins, Fiona, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLloyd, Mona, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLloyd, Moya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMills, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRushing, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchippers, Birgit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWalker, Drew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311078045140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780748678860zCo-access DOI >> cli